<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1363,1895]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,1546,1571]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">Description.</emphasis>
Forewing ɗ 
<quantity box="[490,607,1546,1570]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20mm</quantity>
. Male. Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[808,917,1547,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudoradiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanzanica">
<emphasis box="[808,917,1547,1570]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">tanzanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but wings overall much paler, almost semihyaline. Abdomen of specimen # 
<number box="[492,562,1583,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" value="41295.0">41295</number>
(
<collectionCode box="[577,641,1583,1607]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">ZMB</collectionCode>
) is no longer attached to the specimen and not shown to be mounted on the genitalia slide. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartel" box="[369,521,1618,1642]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" refString="Bartel, M. (1903) Neue aethiopische Arctiidae der Sammlung des Kgl. Museums fur Naturkunde in Berlin. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 16, 170 - 220." type="journal article" year="1903">
Bartel (
<number box="[455,513,1618,1642]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" value="1903.0">1903</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the abdomen as “Hinterleib aben orange Gelb, unten, mit Ausnahme eines Streifen an der Spitze, grau. Segmente 
<number box="[654,730,1655,1679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3 bis 6</number>
mit gleichmässigen schwarzen Binden. Auch an den Seiten ist nur eine Reihe kleiner schwarzer Punkte, die in der grauen Färbung stehen und daher wenig auffallen, vorhanden.” [Abdomen orange yellow above and grey below with the exception of a small stripe at the tip. Segments 
<number box="[1314,1376,1727,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3 to 6</number>
have regular black banding. At the sides there is a line of little black dots which appear barely noticeable on a grey background.] Genitalia: As 
<taxonomicName box="[407,516,1800,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudoradiarctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanzanica">
<emphasis box="[407,516,1800,1823]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="29">tanzanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the juxta is wider and the two long straight narrow extensions reaching at least half length of the uncus. The valva is wider, flatter and apically more setose and the small triangular-like dorsolateral process is much reduced and positioned at approximately half length of valva. Female. Unknown.
</paragraph>
